abstract: In a low-rate world where income is increasingly tough to find, more and more investors are getting into the riskier corners of lending to companies.  A financial watchdog says that might cause problems in financial markets during a downturn.
snippet: In a low-rate world where income is increasingly tough to find, more and more investors are getting into the riskier corners of lending to companies.  A financial watchdog says that might cause problems in financial markets during a downturn.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — In a low-rate world where income is increasingly tough to find, more and more investors are getting into the riskier corners of lending to companies. A financial watchdog says that might cause problems in financial markets during a downturn.
headline_main: Watchdog Warns of Dangers in Riskier Corner of Debt Market
headline_print_headline: Watchdog Warns of Dangers in Riskier Corner of Debt Market

abstract: A man was sentenced Thursday to life in prison for killing an off-duty Chicago police officer who was shot while cleaning the car he had bought for retirement.
snippet: A man was sentenced Thursday to life in prison for killing an off-duty Chicago police officer who was shot while cleaning the car he had bought for retirement.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — A man was sentenced Thursday to life in prison for killing an off-duty Chicago police officer who was shot while cleaning the car he had bought for retirement.
headline_main: Man Gets Life Sentence for Killing Cop Close to Retirement
headline_print_headline: Man Gets Life Sentence for Killing Cop Close to Retirement

abstract: The Trump Administration is threatening to effectively ban a company that makes fish oil pills from fishing in the Chesapeake Bay over mounting concerns from regulators, governors and environmental groups about overfishing.
snippet: The Trump Administration is threatening to effectively ban a company that makes fish oil pills from fishing in the Chesapeake Bay over mounting concerns from regulators, governors and environmental groups about overfishing.
lead_paragraph: NORFOLK, Va. — The Trump Administration is threatening to effectively ban a company that makes fish oil pills from fishing in the Chesapeake Bay over mounting concerns from regulators, governors and environmental groups about overfishing.
headline_main: Fish Oil Firm May Be Barred From Fishing in Chesapeake Bay
headline_print_headline: Fish Oil Firm May Be Barred From Fishing in Chesapeake Bay

lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — If hour one of Thursday’s debate was a substantive if sedate affair, hour two had significant and even sizzling moments for Mayor Pete Buttigieg, Senator Elizabeth Warren and Senator Amy Klobuchar. abstract: Algorithms falsely identified African-American and Asian faces 10 to 100 times more than Caucasian faces, researchers for the National Institute of Standards and Technology found.
snippet: Algorithms falsely identified African-American and Asian faces 10 to 100 times more than Caucasian faces, researchers for the National Institute of Standards and Technology found.
lead_paragraph: The majority of commercial facial-recognition systems exhibit bias, according to a study from a federal agency released on Thursday, underscoring questions about a technology increasingly used by police departments and federal agencies to identify suspected criminals.

abstract: Over nearly a year of tumultuous negotiations, congressional Democrats and the Trump administration bridged what seemed to be an impassable divide.
snippet: Over nearly a year of tumultuous negotiations, congressional Democrats and the Trump administration bridged what seemed to be an impassable divide.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the final days of negotiations over President Trump’s new North American trade deal, Robert Lighthizer, the top trade negotiator, made one more attempt to pressure House Democrats to get on board with the pact. He called Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Saturday saying he had booked a flight to Mexico to sign the revised trade agreement.

abstract: The Democratic-controlled House approved legislation Thursday to suspend for two years the $10,000 cap on state and local tax deductions that came with President Donald Trump’s massive 2017 tax law. The deductions are widely popular, especially in high-tax, heavily Democratic states like New York, New Jersey and California.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic-controlled House approved legislation Thursday to suspend for two years the $10,000 cap on state and local tax deductions that came with President Donald Trump’s massive 2017 tax law. The deductions are widely popular, especially in high-tax, heavily Democratic states like New York, New Jersey and California.
headline_main: House Approves Bill Suspending Cap on Some Tax Deductions
headline_print_headline: House Approves Bill Suspending Cap on Some Tax Deductions
